<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,680]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,186,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Systematic placement.</emphasis>
The last maxillary palpomere securiform, the pronotum with lateral lobes/ apophyses, the abdomen with only eight visible urites, the elongated elytra, and meso- and metatarsal claws simple and without basal tooth, place this new species in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1862" box="[743,821,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Silinae">Silinae</taxonomicName>
and the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Charpentier" authorityYear="1825" box="[994,1042,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[994,1042,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Silis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brancucci, M." box="[1058,1241,258,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" pagination="215 - 388" refId="ref3617" refString="Brancucci, M. (1980) Morphologie comparee, evolution et systematique des Cantharidae (Insecta: Coleoptera), Entomologica Basiliensia, 5, 215 - 388." type="journal article" year="1980">Brancucci 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramsdale, A. S." box="[1254,1432,258,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" pagination="1856" refId="ref4530" refString="Ramsdale, A. S. (2002) Family 64. Cantharidae Imhoff 1856. In: Arnett, R. H. Jr., Thomas, M. C., Skelley, P. E. &amp; Frank, J. H. (Eds.), American Beetles. Vol. 2. Polyphaga: Scarabaeoidea through Curculionoidea. CRC Press, Boca Raton, Florida, pp. 202 - 218." type="book chapter" year="2002">Ramsdale 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Constantin, R." box="[151,339,294,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" pagination="55 - 87" refId="ref3647" refString="Constantin, R. (2009) A contribution to the genus Silis Charpentier, 1825, in Ecuador (Coleoptera, Cantharidae), Entomologica Basiliensia et Collectionis Frey, 31, 55 - 87." type="journal article" year="2009">Constantin 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Constantin, R." box="[350,411,294,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" pagination="41 - 67" refId="ref3766" refString="Constantin, R. (2017) Les Silinae de Guyane avec la description de quatorze especes nouvelles (Coleoptera, Cantharidae), Contribution a l'etude des Coleopteres de Guyane, 11, 41 - 67." type="journal article" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
). Its large size and the lateral margin of its pronotum without a minute glandular tuberosity also place 
<taxonomicName authority="Fanti &amp; Pankowski, 2021" authorityName="FANTI &amp; M. G. PANKOWSKI" authorityYear="2021" box="[269,401,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hegnai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[269,401,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Silis hegnai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[408,497,330,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[408,497,330,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the nominotypical subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Constantin 2009)" baseAuthorityName="Constantin" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[854,1116,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
