<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="166" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,680]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,464,366,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1991" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1991" box="[474,861,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavofemorata">
<emphasis box="[474,688,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Silis flavofemorata</emphasis>
Wittmer, 1991
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[935,1102,366,392]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic is morphologically similar—albeit only vaguely—to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fanti &amp; Pankowski, 2021" authorityName="FANTI &amp; M. G. PANKOWSKI" authorityYear="2021" box="[532,664,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hegnai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[532,664,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Silis hegnai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[672,763,402,428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[672,763,402,428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The new species shows a kind of broad concavity between the two lateral lobes that is not present in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wittmer 1991 a)" baseAuthorityName="Wittmer" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[637,1052,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavofemorata">
<emphasis box="[637,852,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Silis flavofemorata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[868,1044,438,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" pagination="57 - 93" refId="ref4811" refString="Wittmer, W. (1991 a) Zur Kenntnis der Cantharidae (Col.) der Antillen (2. Beitrag). Mitteilungen der Entomologische Gesellschaft Basel, 41 (2 / 3), 57 - 93." type="journal article" year="1991">Wittmer 1991a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wittmer" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[1221,1408,438,465]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavofemorata">
<emphasis box="[1221,1408,438,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">S. flavofemorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smaller in size: 
<quantity box="[327,420,474,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7 mm</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[434,607,474,500]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" pagination="57 - 93" refId="ref4811" refString="Wittmer, W. (1991 a) Zur Kenntnis der Cantharidae (Col.) der Antillen (2. Beitrag). Mitteilungen der Entomologische Gesellschaft Basel, 41 (2 / 3), 57 - 93." type="journal article" year="1991">Wittmer 1991a</bibRefCitation>
). The only other 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Constantin" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[797,845,474,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[797,845,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Silis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in Miocene deposits is 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1963" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiapasensis">
<emphasis box="[1182,1380,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Silis chiapasensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." pageId="3" pageNumber="166" pagination="59" refId="ref4774" refString="Wittmer, W. (1963) A new cantharid from the Chiapas amber of Mexico. University of California Publications in Entomology, 31, 53, pl. 3 (pp. 59)." type="journal article" year="1963">Wittmer, 1963</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Mexican (Chiapas) amber (
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[640,801,510,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" pagination="59" refId="ref4774" refString="Wittmer, W. (1963) A new cantharid from the Chiapas amber of Mexico. University of California Publications in Entomology, 31, 53, pl. 3 (pp. 59)." type="journal article" year="1963">Wittmer 1963</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1963" box="[820,990,510,537]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiapasensis">
<emphasis box="[820,990,510,537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">S. chiapasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Fanti &amp; Pankowski, 2021" authorityName="FANTI &amp; M. G. PANKOWSKI" authorityYear="2021" box="[1136,1266,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hegnai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1136,1266,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Silis hegnai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1273,1362,510,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1273,1362,510,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the former species’ more transverse pronotum and the presence of a spine on each side, as well as for its considerably smaller body size than 
<taxonomicName authority="Fanti &amp; Pankowski, 2021" authorityName="FANTI &amp; M. G. PANKOWSKI" authorityYear="2021" box="[409,541,582,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Silis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hegnai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[409,541,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Silis hegnai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[548,637,582,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[548,637,582,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="166" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,680]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,618,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="166">Remarks.</emphasis>
The amber piece is extremely transparent, measures 20.7 x 15.6 x 
<quantity box="[1074,1161,618,645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2 mm</quantity>
and weighs 
<quantity box="[1304,1433,618,645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.08" pageId="3" pageNumber="166" unit="g" value="1.08">1.08 grams</quantity>
. The inclusion is complete and perfectly visible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
